sentenceData.sentence: In the wake of four years of economic turmoil around the world and political upheaval in a number of nations, very few people are satisfied with the way things are going in their country.
In only six of the 21 nations surveyed do half or more of the population think national economic conditions will improve over the next 12 months.
This includes very optimistic Brazilians (84%), Chinese (83%) and Tunisians (75%) and relatively optimistic Americans (52%), Mexicans (51%) and Egyptians (50%).
In addition, a plurality of Indians (45%) and Turks (44%) see a better economy on the horizon.
\nBut in six countries majorities or pluralities think economic conditions will worsen, including 81% of Greeks and 60% of Czechs.
